    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 26.32,
      "end": 27.52,
      "text": "Asop's Fables.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 28.22,
      "end": 29.4,
      "text": "The horse in his rider.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 30.5,
      "end": 37.1,
      "text": "A young man who fancied himself something of a horseman mounted a horse which had not",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 37.1,
      "end": 42.68,
      "text": "been properly broken in and was exceedingly difficult to control.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 43.38,
      "end": 49.6,
      "text": "No sooner did the horse feel his weight in the saddle than he bolted, and nothing would",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 49.6,
      "end": 50.38,
      "text": "stop him.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 50.38,
      "end": 56.9,
      "text": "A friend of the riders met him in the road and in his headlong career and called out,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 57.56,
      "end": 60.56,
      "text": "where are you off to in such a hurry?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 61.22,
      "end": 66.42,
      "text": "To which he, pointing to the horse, replied, I have no idea.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 67.18,
      "end": 67.8,
      "text": "I ask him.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 69.22,
      "end": 71.96,
      "text": "End of the horse and his rider.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
